layers.name: Coastal Protection Fund
layers.description: After a spill the responsible party is liable for environmental damages to public resources, such as aquatic habitats, beaches, parks, and water quality. The monetary assessment paid by a spiller is deposited into the stateâ€™s coastal protection fund (CPF). A committee of representatives from various state agencies decide how the money is spent - usually selecting resource restoration or enhancement projects in areas affected by the spill.

layers.name: Direct Restoration
layers.description: Direct restoration projects are those funded directly by the responsible party.
